# National Register of Historic Places listings in Richmond County, North Carolina

This page catalogues the properties and historic districts that have been formally recognized on the [National Register of Historic Places](/National_Register_of_Historic_Places) within [Richmond County, North Carolina](/Richmond_County,_North_Carolina). The listings reflect more than two centuries of architectural innovation, economic activity, and cultural significance, ranging from antebellum plantations to early‑twentieth‑century commercial blocks. Each entry includes the official name as it appears on the register, a brief description of its historical and architectural importance, the date of nomination, its precise location, and geographic coordinates. The compilation is current through the National Park Service’s most recent update posted on **December 12, 2025** (see footnote [2] ).  

> *“The National Register evaluates properties according to criteria that emphasize significance in American history, architecture, archaeology, engineering, and culture. Properties must retain sufficient integrity to convey their significance.”* — National Park Service, “[National Register of Historic Places](/National_Register_of_Historic_Places)”, U.S. Department of the Interior  

The following table presents the **Current listings** in alphabetical order by the significant words of each property’s name. For each entry, the coordinates have been derived from the original National Register Information System and have been adjusted to conform to modern GPS standards; minor corrections are indicated in the footnotes.  

